CatDescriptText: Mr. David Woods, janitor, North Side, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 4, 1961, pg. 7 with question "Who do you think is largely responsible for Negro topflight entertainers being denied the chance to headline the Grade A television shows--the sponsors, the advertising agencies, or the general public?"  Answer reads: "It's hard to say, because it covers a large territory...a little bit to blame....They are always giving excuses and passing the buck...."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of David Woods wearing hat, eyeglasses, and zippered jacket, standing on sidewalk with Dimilings Candy in background, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
